Action libraries for CTLedit

Strafer base actions:
-Drive
--Type:Axis
--Description:Forward and backwards movement
-Turn
--Type:Axis
--Description:Turning movement
-Strafe
--Type:Axis
--Description:Left and right movement without turning

fy25 base actions:
-Pivot
--Type:Axis
--Range:-1/1
--Description:Pivot arm up or down
-Set Pivot Position
--Type:Button
--Description:Set the pivot arm to a certain position
--Parameters:
---Position:
----Type:int
----Range:0/2000
-Extend
--Type:Axis
--Range:-0.5/0.5
--Description:Extend arm in or out
-Set Extend Position
--Type:Button
--Description:Extend the arm to a certain position
--Paramters:
---Position:
----Type:int
----Range:0/2000


-----------------------------------------------------------


Method and Action libraries for CTL2Java

Syntax:
-Methods:
--Key is the name of the method.
--Value is the code inside the method.
--Methods are always void. They are added to the generated scheme verbatim, except that items inside of <!> tags are Action names. They are replaced with the Code from that Action.

-Actions:
--Key is the name of the action.
--Value is a dictionary:
---Type: type of primitive to use (Button or Axis)
---Splittable [Axis only]: Can this be assigned to the triggers or 2 buttons?
---Description: A short human-readable description of what this action does on the robot
---Code: The code to drive this action that will be inserted into a Method (If nothing in the Methods library refers to this Action and the Action is assigned, a Method will be created just for it.)


Strafer Base Methods
-buildDTS : "double drive = <!>Drive<!>;
             double turn = <!>Turn<!>;
             double strafe = <!>Strafe<!>;
             controlState.setDts( new DTS( drive, turn, strafe ) );"

Strafer Base Actions
-Drive
--Type : Axis
--Splittable : True
--Description : Forward and backward movement
--Code : !DTS
-Turn
--Type : Axis
--Splittable : True
--Description : Turning
--Code : !DTS
-Strafe
--Type: Axis
--Splittable : True
--Description : Left and right movement without turning
--Code : !DTS




-Drive Power Up
--Type : Button
--Description : Increase maximum drive power
-Drive Power Down
--Type : Button
--Description : Decrease maximum drive power